Altus Biologics, Inc. Appoints Lynne H. Brum To Its Board Of Directors











Tweet








10/19/2005 5:10:56 PM


 CAMBRIDGE, Mass.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--April 15, 2004--Altus(R) Biologics Inc. announced today that Lynne H. Brum has been appointed to its Board of Directors. Ms. Brum is an executive officer of Vertex Pharmaceuticals and a member of the Vertex Pharmaceuticals senior management team. 

 "Lynne brings to Altus's Board a wealth of experience in the strategy and execution of initiatives that are vital to the success of innovative, high-growth companies," said Peter Lanciano, Chairman of the Board, President and CEO of Altus. "As Altus transitions to focus on the development of multiple products for gastrointestinal and metabolic diseases, Lynne's strategic planning abilities and expertise in corporate communications and finance will play a critical role in supporting our efforts."   Ms. Brum is Vertex's Vice President of Corporate Communications and Financial Planning. In this capacity, she leads the Company's financial planning group as well as its corporate communications, investor relations and media relations initiatives. During her tenure at Vertex, she has held a variety of management positions in corporate communications, product marketing and corporate development. Ms. Brum has more than 16 years experience in the biotech industry leading the areas of investor relations, product communications, financial planning and financing. Ms. Brum joined Vertex in 1994 from Feinstein Kean Healthcare. Ms. Brum holds an M.B.A. from the Simmons Graduate School of Management, and a B.A. in biological sciences from Wellesley College. 

Altus is a pharmaceutical company that uses its proprietary protein crystallization technology to develop innovative, orally delivered enzyme replacement therapies to treat a number of significant unmet medical needs in the areas of gastrointestinal and metabolic diseases. Altus' protein crystallization technology, known as Crystalomics(TM), enables the rapid commercialization of high-value orally delivered protein-based products by creating highly stable and potent protein therapeutics. The technology enables oral delivery of the protein to the gastrointestinal tract to provide a localized or topical effect within the gastrointestinal lumen. These products are novel therapies that are designed to be safe, effective and convenient for patients. Through its product portfolio, the Company's vision is to be the worldwide leader in the rapid and efficient development of valuable oral enzyme replacement therapies for the treatment of gastrointestinal and metabolic diseases. The Company has a series of products in various stages of research and development, all leveraging the Crystalomics technology. Altus has numerous development partners and is constantly evaluating the opportunity to expand its product development efforts through partnering opportunities.    Contacts          Altus Biologics Inc. Robert Gallotto, 617-299-2952 rgallotto@altus.com     






