Lynne H. Brum – Secretary
 Vice President, Vertex Pharmaceuticals Incorporated, Cambridge, MA
 Lynne is Vice President of Corporate Communications and Market Development at Vertex Pharmaceuticals Incorporated located in Cambridge, Massachusetts. Vertex is a leading emerging pharmaceutical company with one therapeutic product on the market and eight in clinical trials. At Vertex she manages all of the company’s investor relations, media relations and product communications activities. Lynne has played a key role in the strategy and execution of Vertex’s financing activities including three common stock offerings totaling $270 million as well as the company’s recent $175 million offering of subordinated convertible notes. From 1994 to March 2000, Vertex’s market capitalization increased from $300 million to $2 billion. Lynne joined Vertex in 1994 from Feinstein Kean Partners Inc. (FKP), a corporate communications and investor relations consulting firm where she was a vice president. The practice focused on private and newly public biotech companies. Previously, she held corporate communications and research positions at Biogen, Inc. Lynne has fourteen years experience specializing in corporate and strategic communications for biotechnology companies.
Lynne holds a Masters of Business Administration from the Simmons Graduate School of Management, and a B.A. in Biological Sciences from Wellesley College.


